package: Stereo Ergonomics mode
author: Ben Dickson (Rising Sun Pictures)
contact: ben.dickson@rsp.com.au
version: 1.0
rv: 3.12.13

modes:
  - file: stereoergo.py
    load: immediate

description: |
    <p>
    Prevents RSI.
    </p>

    <p>
    Err, more helpfully.. In stereo hotkeys mode (Alt+s to enable):

    <ul>
    <li>Shift+left/right adjusts convergence</li>
    <li>Shift+up toggles scanline-interleave mode</li>
    <li>Shift+down toggles anaglyph mode (and greyscale)</li>
    <li>Up-arrow cycles between eyes (same with down arrow)</li>
    <li>Page-up and Page-down step through frames then eyes (frame1-left, frame1-right, frame2-left, frame2-right etc)</li>
    </li>
    </ul>
    </p>
